259
00:14:51,941 --> 00:14:53,741
No, not everyone is!

260
00:14:54,011 --> 00:14:55,811
Kohsaka buys it too, naturally.

261
00:14:55,911 --> 00:14:56,941
That I do!

262
00:14:58,921 --> 00:15:02,681
Um, if you want titles geared
towards women, we have better ones.

263
00:15:02,891 --> 00:15:04,511
Don't bring those up!

264
00:15:04,721 --> 00:15:05,451
Show me!

265
00:15:10,361 --> 00:15:12,061
Are you for real?

266
00:15:12,561 --> 00:15:13,861
Isn't he... you know?

267
00:15:14,031 --> 00:15:16,901
...and he's the vocalist from...

268
00:15:17,001 --> 00:15:18,871
These don't belong to me personally...

269
00:15:18,941 --> 00:15:19,701
Whoa!

270
00:15:20,701 --> 00:15:24,611
You know, I think I really
am a little interested now.

271
00:15:25,511 --> 00:15:26,981
Y-You suppose her eyes just opened?

272
00:15:27,541 --> 00:15:30,031
I can't wait for Comic Fest!

273
00:15:38,091 --> 00:15:40,061
Why've things turned
out like this, again?

274
00:15:40,121 --> 00:15:42,611
Yeah, why's Sistah here?

275
00:15:42,731 --> 00:15:43,781
You're one to talk!

276
00:15:44,591 --> 00:15:48,891
Needless to say, I don't have one bit
of an inkling to become an otaku.

277
00:15:49,601 --> 00:15:52,001
I'm only here to keep an eye on her.

278
00:15:52,441 --> 00:15:53,801
Do you get that?

279
00:15:53,941 --> 00:15:55,061
You do, right?

280
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:56,571
Of course we do.

281
00:15:56,941 --> 00:15:58,501
How childish.

282
00:15:58,811 --> 00:16:01,681
Someone has to teach kids
how rough the world is.

283
00:16:02,051 --> 00:16:06,481
Well, we understand that
plenty, but we can't help you.

284
00:16:06,621 --> 00:16:08,411
We'll have our hands full shopping.

285
00:16:08,521 --> 00:16:09,041
Right.

286
00:16:09,421 --> 00:16:12,791
I know, which is why I
won't let her slip away.

287
00:16:12,921 --> 00:16:15,321
As if I'd slip away from Kohsaka.

288
00:16:16,031 --> 00:16:17,821
Don't let it go to your head!

289
00:16:17,961 --> 00:16:19,661
It's not?

290
00:16:19,801 --> 00:16:21,891
She's not slipping away...

291
00:16:22,631 --> 00:16:23,761
Yeah...

292
00:16:32,641 --> 00:16:33,631
Hey...

293
00:16:33,811 --> 00:16:34,671
Yeah?

294
00:16:35,141 --> 00:16:38,771
Why are they lined up in the
middle of this goddamned heat?

295
00:16:39,551 --> 00:16:41,041
How should I know?

296
00:16:43,891 --> 00:16:47,751
Ahh, the ones up front are
finally starting to stand up...

297
00:16:48,191 --> 00:16:49,921
Wonder if they'll move...

298
00:16:50,061 --> 00:16:52,361
I'm about to have a nosebleed...

299
00:16:53,861 --> 00:16:55,161
Oh, okay.

300
00:16:55,471 --> 00:16:56,521
Gotcha.

301
00:16:56,971 --> 00:16:59,701
They say they'll meet up
with us once we've moved some.

302
00:17:00,441 --> 00:17:03,741
Man, their type sure is crafty.

303
00:17:07,811 --> 00:17:09,781
Please keep off the grass.

304
00:17:09,911 --> 00:17:10,641
Huh?

305
00:17:10,781 --> 00:17:14,111
The lawn is all off-limits.
Please come over here at once.

306
00:17:34,771 --> 00:17:35,831
Kohsaka!

307
00:17:35,911 --> 00:17:37,131
Kohsaka!

308
00:17:37,741 --> 00:17:38,711
Kohsaka?

309
00:17:39,041 --> 00:17:40,571
H-How far are you gonna go?

310
00:17:41,041 --> 00:17:43,511
The lines for the biggest
circles are outside.

311
00:18:05,801 --> 00:18:09,861
Why do they do something like...

312
00:18:10,541 --> 00:18:14,531
Don't you think becoming
an otaku ain't worth it?

313
00:18:19,251 --> 00:18:20,651
No, I'll do it!

314
00:18:20,751 --> 00:18:23,151
I've got what it takes, I know it!

315
00:18:25,121 --> 00:18:26,881
Someone in our group said this...

316
00:18:28,961 --> 00:18:31,721
An otaku isn't something
you try to become...

317
00:18:32,661 --> 00:18:34,651
You just are one before you know it...

318
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:47,201
That's why you can't quit either.

319
00:18:47,311 --> 00:18:51,581
It's laughable, but
for us it's a tragedy.

320
00:18:52,751 --> 00:18:56,481
You don't really get what it
means to go out with an otaku.

321
00:18:58,121 --> 00:19:01,721
It's not as if it's enough to
say you'll just become one too...

322
00:19:02,791 --> 00:19:03,951
What're you saying?

323
00:19:05,061 --> 00:19:07,191
In my opinion...

324
00:19:08,261 --> 00:19:09,231
Nah, I won't tell you.

325
00:19:09,771 --> 00:19:11,101
That's unfair!

326
00:19:11,201 --> 00:19:12,931
You're my rival, idiot.

327
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:14,561
Like I'd tell you.

328
00:19:30,891 --> 00:19:33,791
Did you see all those dojinshi
for sale on the way here?

329
00:19:33,961 --> 00:19:35,981
It's an incredible world.

330
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:38,081
I totally didn't have time to...

331
00:19:38,191 --> 00:19:39,661
Then let's go see.

332
00:19:39,801 --> 00:19:41,731
I totally don't have the willpower...

333
00:19:42,031 --> 00:19:43,931
You don't have a thing.

334
00:19:44,031 --> 00:19:45,331
I totally don't...

335
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:48,131
Please don't sit on the grass.

336
00:19:50,741 --> 00:19:51,601
Hi.

337
00:19:51,771 --> 00:19:53,261
Oh? What happened to those two?

338
00:19:53,641 --> 00:19:56,111
We got separated so I called them.

339
00:19:56,181 --> 00:19:57,911
They said they'll be at the
restaurant down at that end...

340
00:19:58,011 --> 00:19:59,881
...and for us to call
them when we leave.

341
00:19:59,981 --> 00:20:02,851
Just tell them to go home already.

342
00:20:03,051 --> 00:20:04,581
What the hell'd they come for anyway?

343
00:20:05,021 --> 00:20:08,791
This is a letdown, since
Kasukabe comes here so rarely.

344
00:20:08,961 --> 00:20:12,831
It's a mistake in itself for them
to come when they don't even fit in!

345
00:20:12,961 --> 00:20:14,191
That's true.

346
00:20:15,201 --> 00:20:16,631
But you know...

347
00:20:17,871 --> 00:20:21,771
Now we can admire the booty
to our hearts' content.

348
00:20:22,311 --> 00:20:24,001
How about the new Jam Jam Bullet?

349
00:20:24,171 --> 00:20:26,161
Here it is, I bought it.

350
00:20:26,681 --> 00:20:29,141
We sure bought a lot this time.

351
00:20:47,061 --> 00:20:50,831
You mean you've never thought of
becoming an otaku for Kohsaka's sake?

352
00:20:50,931 --> 00:20:52,061
Never.

353
00:20:52,801 --> 00:20:56,901
Well, I did at least try a video
game with him once, but that bombed.

354
00:20:57,411 --> 00:20:59,201
Then you have tried.

355
00:20:59,411 --> 00:21:00,881
So, do you understand now?

356
00:21:01,711 --> 00:21:02,841
What?

357
00:21:03,351 --> 00:21:04,681
Give me a hint.

358
00:21:04,811 --> 00:21:05,301
No.

359
00:21:05,411 --> 00:21:07,641
Why not?

360
00:21:08,421 --> 00:21:10,611
People sure get crabby
when they get old.

361
00:21:11,121 --> 00:21:11,681
Ow!

362
00:21:26,901 --> 00:21:30,241
It was just a typical Comic
Fest for us, in the end.

363
00:21:30,441 --> 00:21:31,871
That it was.

364
00:21:32,811 --> 00:21:34,971
But maybe we got to buy more this time?

365
00:21:35,441 --> 00:21:36,911
Hey, Keiko.

366
00:21:37,281 --> 00:21:38,011
Huh?

367
00:21:38,111 --> 00:21:39,981
How long are you going
to be at my place?

368
00:21:40,281 --> 00:21:42,651
Oh, I'll leave today.

369
00:21:43,791 --> 00:21:45,911
Oh yeah?
Is that so...

370
00:21:46,021 --> 00:21:48,851
You're a total gimp.
How long have we been related?

371
00:21:49,331 --> 00:21:51,691
You bought a ton of dirty
stuff today, didn't you?

372
00:21:54,461 --> 00:21:57,731
I could do without an
actual little sister...

373
00:21:57,831 --> 00:21:58,771
You think?

374
00:21:58,871 --> 00:22:00,361
There's nothing good about them.

375
00:22:01,941 --> 00:22:04,061
So you do understand.

376
00:22:04,441 --> 00:22:05,171
Understand what?

377
00:22:05,271 --> 00:22:06,741
How to date an otaku.

378
00:22:07,381 --> 00:22:08,431
That's it.

379
00:22:08,741 --> 00:22:11,801
What, you mean like this?

380
00:22:11,981 --> 00:22:12,451
Yup!

381
00:22:12,521 --> 00:22:14,281
Then today, you too...

382
00:22:17,991 --> 00:22:19,821
Yeah, I'll go back
to my place, of course.

383
00:22:21,261 --> 00:22:23,491
Ouch, that's rough.

384
00:22:24,061 --> 00:22:27,031
Well, it's about valuing
your time alone...

385
00:22:27,761 --> 00:22:31,031
Yeah but, I mean, isn't
that like being cheated on?

386
00:22:31,801 --> 00:22:33,101
It is...

387
00:22:34,241 --> 00:22:36,261
You're something else, sistah.

388
00:22:36,441 --> 00:22:38,241
Admiration doesn't make me happy.

389
00:22:39,111 --> 00:22:41,101
In that case let me
stay at your place...

390
00:22:41,281 --> 00:22:42,141
Go home!

391
00:22:42,281 --> 00:22:43,781
What was that for?

392
00:22:43,781 --> 00:22:45,441
<i>I guess they get along now?
What was that for?</i>

393
00:22:45,551 --> 00:22:47,281
That can't be a good thing...

394
00:22:47,351 --> 00:22:52,311
Hey, you don't suppose your sister
will get into our school next year?

395
00:22:52,391 --> 00:22:54,981
No, she's an idiot.
We're in the clear.

396
00:22:55,091 --> 00:22:55,921
Pardon?

397
00:23:06,801 --> 00:23:15,841
<i>We took no detours or shortcuts...</i>

398
00:23:16,211 --> 00:23:25,181
<i>... and we weren't afraid of
what tomorrow would bring...</i>

399
00:23:25,491 --> 00:23:34,451
<i>... as we kept walking down
Inogashira Street late at night.</i>

400
00:23:34,901 --> 00:23:44,201
<i>Only vivid dreams extended
deep into the shadows.</i>

401
00:23:45,371 --> 00:23:54,581
<i>We aren't quite grown up.</i>

402
00:23:55,821 --> 00:24:06,061
<i>Simple but complicated
glistening like marbles.</i>

403
00:24:06,331 --> 00:24:15,531
<i>The time we spied from there sparkled,
even if nothing big happened.</i>

404
00:24:15,841 --> 00:24:25,511
<i>What we see from the marbles in
our hands now is a little different...</i>

405
00:24:25,651 --> 00:24:34,391
<i>... but they shine faintly nearby.</i>

406
00:24:41,001 --> 00:24:43,121
Saki, why do you hate otaku?

407
00:24:43,231 --> 00:24:44,101
Because they're homely.

408
00:24:44,201 --> 00:24:47,901
They're fat, they wear bandanas and
weird gloves, have bags full of junk...

409
00:24:47,971 --> 00:24:49,601
Lately more of them
have been attractive.

410
00:24:49,871 --> 00:24:52,841
I don't know, but you can tell them by
their stench, that super strong smell.

411
00:24:52,981 --> 00:24:54,911
And they're so proud
when they take a bath.

412
00:24:55,011 --> 00:24:57,071
Like that's some extraordinary thing.
It's nothing to be "proud" of.

413
00:24:57,151 --> 00:24:57,911
Um, well...

414
00:24:57,981 --> 00:24:59,111
And what's with their conversations?

415
00:24:59,181 --> 00:25:01,151
Did you know this, did you know that?

416
00:25:01,251 --> 00:25:03,621
That's not conversation, it's just a
bragging fest. What are they, idiots?

417
00:25:03,891 --> 00:25:05,251
Keep your voices down,
stop talking to yourselves...

418
00:25:05,321 --> 00:25:06,451
...don't get so friendly
with me, get lost!

419
00:25:06,591 --> 00:25:07,391
Aww.

420
00:25:07,491 --> 00:25:09,351
Don't say things like that!

